WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:27.160 --> 00:00:36.380
The Yellow River, Huang He, is 5,464 kilometres long, ranking fifth in the world.

00:00:38.400 --> 00:00:43.780
Originating in the Qinghai Tibetan Plateau,
it flows east through nine provinces

00:00:43.780 --> 00:00:46.500
and empties into the Bohai Sea.

00:01:03.480 --> 00:01:08.240
Sometimes Huang He is poetically
called the 'Muddy Flow'.

00:01:09.920 --> 00:01:16.740
The rich silt carried by Huang He formed fertile farmland that is the birthplace of Chinese culture.

00:01:35.220 --> 00:01:40.560
The earliest characters, villages, cities
and drawings originated here.

00:02:13.440 --> 00:02:19.220
Huang He is regarded as the 'Mother of China'.

